Syntax: emote <message>
Syntax: : <message>
Syntax: , <message>

The emote command allows you to display whatever you want to the other users
in the room.  What is displayed will be your name followed by the <message>.
You may use ':' or ',' as short cuts for the emote command.

eg. if JoeBlow typed emote jumps up and down excitedLY!
Each user in the room then sees:
JoeBlow jumps up and down excitedLY!

Emotes are considered a form of communications and is subject to the various
problems and results that communications may cause.  Emote presumes that an
action is taking place, as such, it is hard to emote when drunk.  

